-- Petronas Carigali Says 6 Injured During Fire at Oil Platform Off Malaysia
-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 2010-12-14T04:38:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/petronas-carigali-says-6-injured-during-fire-at-oil-platform-off-malaysia.html
Petronas Carigali Sdn. , a unit of
Malaysia’s state oil company, said six people were injured when
a fire broke out at its platform off Peninsular Malaysia.  “There were a total of 108 personnel on the platform when
the incident happened,” the company said in a statement sent
from Kuala Lumpur today. The fire, which occurred during
scheduled maintenance, was extinguished this morning. The
remaining workers were evacuated to nearby platforms, the
company said.  Petronas Carigali said it is investigating the cause of the
incident.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chong Pooi Koon in Kuala Lumpur at 
